lead_paragraph: Kemba Walker had 40 points and nine assists, and Spencer Hawes made a go-ahead 3-poiner with 17 seconds left in overtime to rally the Charlotte Hornets to a 120-116 victory over the Orlando Magic on Friday night.

headline.print_headline: Walker Leads Hornets to 120-116 OT Win Over Magic
